<TITLE> ETV journalists transferred to CMH </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 19(bdnews24.com)Two ETV newsmen, injured in a road accident while covering Khaleda Zia's election campaign in the north, were admitted to Dhaka Combined Military Hospital on Friday evening. Special correspondent Rashed Ahmed and photographer Asaduzzaman were admitted to CMH after being transferred from a Bogra hospital, a senior correspondent of the channel told bdnews24.com. "They are being kept under observation in Intensive Care Unit-1," Konok Soroar said. The microbus carrying the ETV crew plunged into a roadside ditch, after colliding with a bus, as it was following the BNP chairperson's motorcade on Wednesday. The two journalists and the microbus driver were wounded in the head-on crash at Raiganj in Sirajganj and rushed to a local hospital. They were admitted to Bogra Ziaur Rahman Medical College Hospital, where Rashed Ahmed underwent surgery on broken facial bones. Soroar said the driver Rabiul Islam remains at Bogra Medical College Hospital. b
